// Atlantis Track 09 — Views P-6 (design §9): JsonValue number rendering. `toJson`'d
// int fields should print `3` not `3.0` through the Track 09 formatter, per the
// design's own instruction: if not, COORDINATE before writing a local formatter — never
// shim it. Finding recorded in the design's §13 log (this is a real, pre-existing,
// documented limitation — reference.md §6.11 already pins "42.000000" as the v1 wire
// format, revisited only when float formatting is addressed globally, §19).
void main() {
    console.writeln(JsonValue::ofNum(3.0).render());
    console.writeln(JsonValue::ofNum(0.0).render());
    console.writeln(JsonValue::ofNum(3.5).render());
}
main();
